            <!-- Foil Test -->
            <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-xl p-6 border-l-4 border-cyan-500">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-900 mb-2">The Foil Test — Prove It's a Leak, Not Condensation</h3>
              <p class="text-cyan-800 mb-3">
                Builder claims it's just condensation? Do this simple test:
              </p>
              <ol class="space-y-2 text-cyan-900 text-sm ml-6">
                <li>1. Dry the damp area completely with a towel</li>
                <li>2. Tape a 12" x 12" piece of aluminum foil to the wall, sealing all edges with tape</li>
                <li>3. Wait 24-48 hours</li>
                <li>4. Remove the foil and check:</li>
              </ol>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-cyan-900 text-sm ml-12 mt-2">
                <li>• Moisture on the ROOM side of foil = condensation (humidity in your air)</li>
                <li>• Moisture BEHIND the foil (wall side) = water infiltration through foundation</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-cyan-800 mt-3 text-sm">
                Take photos and include this test in your Tarion claim.
              </p>
            </div>
